{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"The Avro side is clearer now: `AvroJob` stores the data model class name in Hadoop `Configuration`, then reloads it by name and reflectively invokes a `ClassLoader` constructor. That means `ReflectData` likely needs both runtime class reachability and constructor registration, not just a marker entry."}}
